      • getSendingTime

        public IValue getSendingTime(boolean numeric,
                             UTCTimePrecision precision)
        Returns the current time as an IValue.
        Parameters:
        numeric - If true, the returned IValue is populated with a long of the requested precision, otherwise a FIX string is used.
        precision - precision
        Returns:
        An IValue containing either a FIX formatted time as a String or the number of time units since the Epoch, according to the specified precision.

      • getSendingTimeBytes

        public byte[] getSendingTimeBytes(UTCTimePrecision precision)
        Return the FIX UTC date/time encoded according to the specified precision.

        The returned byte array contains one of the following:

        • datetime: yyyyMMdd-HH:mm:ss (seconds precision)}, OR
        • datetime.millis: yyyyMMdd-HH:mm:ss.SSS (milliseconds precision), OR
        • datetime.millis: yyyyMMdd-HH:mm:ss.SSSSSS (microseconds precision), OR
        • datetime.millis: yyyyMMdd-HH:mm:ss.SSSSSSSSS (nanoseconds precision)
        Parameters:
        precision - The required precision.
        Returns:
        The FIX UTC date/time according to the specified precision.

      • getSendingTimeBytes

        public byte[] getSendingTimeBytes()
        Return the current encoded FIX UTC date/time encoded to second precision.
        Returns:
        The current encoded FIX UTC date/time encoded to second precision.

      • getSendingTimeBytes

        @Deprecated
public byte[] getSendingTimeBytes(boolean isMilli)
        Deprecated. Use getSendingTimeBytes(UTCTimePrecision) instead.
        Return the current encoded FIX UTC date/time.

        The returned byte array contains one of the following:

        • datetime: yyyyMMdd-HH:mm:ss, OR
        • datetime.millis: yyyyMMdd-HH:mm:ss.SSS
        Parameters:
        isMilli - True to include millisecond precision in the encoded date/time, false to stop at second precision.
        Returns:
        The current encoded FIX UTC date/time.

      • getDateTimeBytes

        @Deprecated
public byte[] getDateTimeBytes(boolean isDate,
                                           boolean isMilli)
        Deprecated. For obtaining FIX date only bytes use getDateBytes() instead. For obtaining FIX date/time bytes use getSendingTimeBytes(UTCTimePrecision) instead.
        Return a byte array containing one of the following:

        date: yyyyMMdd

        datetime: yyyyMMdd-HH:mm:ss

        datetime.millis yyyyMMdd-HH:mm:ss.SSS

        Parameters:
        isDate - true returns the date, else the return is controlled by isMilli
        isMilli - true returns datetime, else datetime.millis.
        Returns:
        byte[] containing the selected current date or datetime.
